Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease glass loaf pan. Mix first 9 ingredients in large bowl. Combine buttermilk, molasses, oil and egg in another bowl and whisk to blend. Add to dry ingredients and stir until just blended. Spoon into prepared pan. Bake until springy to touch, about 50 minutes. Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes. Turn out onto rack and cool completely. (Can be prepared up to 1 day ahead. Cover tightly.)
